      <h2 id="content-calendar">HVAC Content Calendar Template</h2>
      
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Successful HVAC companies plan content 30-60 days ahead using seasonal themes, local events, and industry awareness days. Here's a proven content calendar framework:</p>
        
        <h3>Monthly Content Themes</h3>
        
        <p><strong>January:</strong> Indoor air quality focus, humidifier maintenance, heating efficiency tips<br>
        <strong>February:</strong> Preventive maintenance prep, carbon monoxide awareness<br>
        <strong>March:</strong> Spring HVAC preparation, duct cleaning season<br>
        <strong>April-May:</strong> AC preparation, air filter campaigns, cooling system tune-ups<br>
        <strong>June-August:</strong> Emergency response capability, energy efficiency tips<br>
        <strong>September:</strong> Heating system preparation, thermostat programming<br>
        <strong>October-November:</strong> Furnace maintenance, winter preparation<br>
        <strong>December:</strong> Holiday emergency coverage, year-end maintenance specials</p>
        
        <h3>Weekly Posting Schedule</h3>
        
        <p>Most successful HVAC companies follow this posting pattern:</p>
        
        <p><strong>Monday:</strong> Motivational team content or weekend emergency calls<br>
        <strong>Tuesday:</strong> Educational content (how-to tips, maintenance advice)<br>
        <strong>Wednesday:</strong> Customer spotlight or testimonial<br>
        <strong>Thursday:</strong> Behind-the-scenes content or equipment focus<br>
        <strong>Friday:</strong> Before/after project photos or team highlights<br>
        <strong>Saturday:</strong> Community involvement or personal team content<br>
        <strong>Sunday:</strong> Industry news or seasonal preparation tips</p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="lead-generation">Social Media Lead Generation Tactics</h2>
      
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Converting social media followers into paying customers requires specific tactics beyond posting content. The most successful HVAC companies use these lead generation strategies:</p>
        
        <h3>Call-to-Action Optimization</h3>
        
        <p>Every social media post should include a clear next step. High-converting CTAs for HVAC include:</p>
        
        <p><strong>"Call now for 24/7 emergency service"</strong> (45% higher call volume)<br>
        <strong>"Schedule your $89 tune-up today"</strong> (specific pricing converts 23% better)<br>
        <strong>"Get your free estimate in 24 hours"</strong> (time-specific promises increase response)<br>
        <strong>"Download our seasonal maintenance checklist"</strong> (lead magnets capture contact info)</p>
        
        <h3>Social Media Contest Strategy</h3>
        
        <p>HVAC companies running quarterly contests see 67% higher engagement and generate 34% more leads. Effective contest ideas include:</p>
        
        <p><strong>Free Annual Maintenance:</strong> Ask followers to share posts and tag friends for a chance to win free tune-up service worth $150-200.<br>
        <strong>Thermostat Upgrade:</strong> Give away smart thermostats (cost: $200-300) in exchange for email signups and social follows.<br>
        <strong>Energy Efficiency Audit:</strong> Offer comprehensive home energy assessments as prizes for photo contests or referral campaigns.</p>
        
        <h3>Local Community Engagement</h3>
        
        <p>Active participation in local Facebook groups generates 3x more qualified leads than company page posts alone. Join neighborhood groups, homeowner associations, and local business networks. Provide helpful advice without direct selling to build reputation and generate referrals.</p>
      </div>

